          <text>
                    <body>
                              <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Boston</placeName>, <date>Nov. 6<hi
                                                  rend="sup">th</hi> 1851</date>.</p>
                              <p><addressee>Mr. Isaac Leeser</addressee>,</p>
                              <p rend="indent(2)">Dear Sir,</p>
                              <p rend="indent(3)">The Parcel you<lb/> sent me some time ago, I
                                        have<lb/> received, and would have written<lb/> to you ere
                                        this, had it not been<lb/> for some difficulty that exists between<lb/>
                                        <persName>Mr. Strouse</persName> and the Congregation
                                        over<lb/> which he officiates, under the circum-<lb/>stances
                                        I did not feel justified in<lb/> giving him those books
                                        which you<lb/> sent for him, those school Books<lb/> I mean,
                                        please let me know, if<lb/> you wish me to give them to
                                        him<lb/> and also <sic>wheather</sic> I shall collect<lb/>
                                        the money for them. <persName>Mr. Milkman</persName><lb/>
                                        does not want the Prayer Book you<lb/> sent for him, but
                                        will take a<lb/>
                                        <sic>german</sic> one, please write me the<lb/> price of the
                                        german ones, as you did<lb/> not state in your letter what
                                        you sold<lb/> them at, as I have sold two or three of<lb/>
                                        them, also what I shall do with the<lb/> Book you intended
                                        for <persName>Mr Milkman</persName>.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(9)">Yours respectfully</p>
                              <p rend="indent(10)">
                                        <persName role="author">Henry S. Spier</persName>
                              </p>
                              <p>Please correct my name on the cover<lb/> of the occident</p>
                              <p rend="The following lines are written sideways in the left column"
                                        >I have also those Back Nos. of the Occident, which<lb/>
                                        <persName>Mr. Milkman</persName> refuses to take, subject to
                                        your order, he tells<lb/> me he has written to you.</p>
                    </body>
